WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:20.560
7. A Terrible Year 1992 was a very bad year for the royal family.

00:20.560 --> 00:27.160
In January, holiday photographs of Fergie and Steve Wyatt appeared in the newspapers.

00:27.160 --> 00:33.240
The British people were shocked. Fergie's marriage to Prince Andrew was finished.

00:33.240 --> 00:37.920
Wyatt went back to America. Then Fergie became friends with an American

00:37.920 --> 00:46.280
called John Bryan. In February, Charles and Diana went to India.

00:46.280 --> 00:51.880
Photographers took pictures of Diana in front of the Taj Mahal. The history of the Taj Mahal

00:51.880 --> 00:59.240
is very romantic. An Indian emperor built it for his dead wife. Diana sat in front of

00:59.240 --> 01:09.120
it alone. Charles was at a business meeting. On the 29th of March, Diana's father Johnny

01:09.120 --> 01:13.760
died suddenly. Diana was on a skiing holiday with Charles

01:13.760 --> 01:20.080
and the boys in Austria. Her father's death was a terrible shock.

01:20.240 --> 01:26.960
Diana flew back to London. On the 1st of April, Diana drove to Allthorpe for the funeral,

01:26.960 --> 01:34.800
the ceremony for a dead person, and Charles came later by helicopter. Diana did not like

01:34.800 --> 01:42.200
Rain, Johnny's wife, but at the funeral she spoke to Rain and held her hand. After this,

01:42.200 --> 01:49.600
Diana's relationship with Rain was better. Andrew Morton's book about Diana was ready.

01:50.240 --> 01:58.240
He called it Diana, her true story. Diana wanted the British people to know the truth

01:58.240 --> 02:05.880
about her life. But now she was worried. The royal family did not know anything about the book.

02:05.880 --> 02:15.600
Perhaps the book was not a good idea. On the 7th of June, 1992, the Sunday Times newspaper

02:15.760 --> 02:21.920
printed a part of Andrew Morton's book. For the first time, people read about Diana's

02:21.920 --> 02:28.960
bulimia. They read about Charles and Camilla. They learned how Charles was cold to Diana.

02:30.400 --> 02:35.440
Now people could not believe in the royal fairy story. They were very shocked.

02:37.360 --> 02:43.920
The British people began to dislike Prince Charles. Charles is a bad husband and not a very good

02:44.000 --> 02:51.280
father, they said. He doesn't care about Diana. He only cares about himself and Camilla Parker

02:51.280 --> 02:59.600
Bowles. The royal family asked questions. Andrew Morton did not write this book alone,

02:59.600 --> 03:06.400
they said. So Diana's friends talked to him. But did Diana know about this book?

03:06.400 --> 03:13.840
The husband of Diana's sister Jane was Robert Fellows, private secretary to the queen.

03:13.840 --> 03:25.040
Did you know about Andrew Morton's book? He asked Diana. No, replied Diana. Fellows believed her,

03:25.040 --> 03:32.960
but later he found out the truth. Diana became more popular because of Andrew Morton's book.

03:33.920 --> 03:38.800
At the end of June, 1992, she went to Belfast in Northern Ireland.

03:39.680 --> 03:43.680
We want die. We want die, shouted the people.

03:45.280 --> 03:52.080
In August, 1992, the Sun newspaper printed stories about Diana and James Gilby,

03:52.080 --> 03:59.440
and Diana and James Hewitt. Later, Diana and Charles went to Korea. But the visit was not

03:59.440 --> 04:07.760
successful. Charles and Diana did not look happy together. In November, Diana went to Paris alone.

04:09.360 --> 04:15.440
The problems between Charles and Diana grew worse. On the 25th of November,

04:15.440 --> 04:22.480
they met at Kensington Palace and talked about a separation. On the 9th of December,

04:22.480 --> 04:26.560
the Prime Minister John Major gave a speech to the British Parliament.

04:27.520 --> 04:35.440
The prince and princess of Wales have decided to separate, he said, but they had no plans to divorce.

04:37.440 --> 04:45.040
In her Christmas speech at the end of the year, the queen called 1992 a horrible year for the royal family.

04:57.360 --> 05:01.040
Chapter 8. Princess Alone

05:02.960 --> 05:07.120
Diana was now alone, and she wanted a normal private life.

05:08.640 --> 05:13.040
Because she was the princess of Wales, she had a policeman with her all the time,

05:13.760 --> 05:21.920
but now Diana decided she did not need a policeman. Without a policeman, it was easy for the newspaper

05:21.920 --> 05:28.000
reporters and photographers to follow her. They waited for her outside Kensington Palace.

05:28.880 --> 05:35.760
They waited for her when she went out in London. They waited for her at airports when she went on holiday.

05:37.600 --> 05:42.480
Diana's sons, Prince William and Prince Harry, were the centre of her life.

05:43.760 --> 05:50.400
Diana was a very good mother. She wanted William and Harry to have a normal life and to have fun

05:50.400 --> 05:55.840
like other children. So she took them out to the cinema or McDonald's or shopping.

05:57.280 --> 06:00.960
She did not want them to see only rich people like the royal family.

06:02.160 --> 06:08.080
She wanted them to meet people in the normal world too, people with sad and difficult lives.

06:09.520 --> 06:16.160
She took William to the Passage Day Centre in London. The centre was a place for people who live on the

06:16.160 --> 06:23.680
streets. William met the people there and talked to them. William was only a young boy,

06:24.480 --> 06:28.480
but he was like Diana. He was very good at talking to people.

06:30.080 --> 06:33.600
Later Diana took Harry to the centre for homeless people too.

06:35.760 --> 06:40.160
When William and Harry were at home with her, Diana spent a lot of time with them.

06:40.800 --> 06:47.360
But most of the time they were away at boarding school. Then Diana was lonely at home by herself.

06:49.120 --> 06:56.320
Soon Diana met a new man, Oliver Hall. Oliver Hall was very good looking and popular.

06:57.200 --> 07:06.160
He knew a lot about art and bought and sold Islamic art. He was married. Oliver and his wife were

07:06.160 --> 07:13.040
friends of Prince Charles. Poor and Diana talked to each other on the phone and met at Diana's

07:13.040 --> 07:22.000
friend's houses. Diana was still doing her charity work. In March 1993 she visited Nepal.

07:22.720 --> 07:28.960
In July she visited Zimbabwe. She visited a hospital where there were children with AIDS.

07:29.600 --> 07:37.040
The children were only five years old, but they had no parents. Diana cried when she saw them.

07:38.080 --> 07:42.080
She went to the countryside and gave food to poor and hungry children.

07:44.080 --> 07:52.720
At home Diana became interested in women's problems. In April 1993 she gave a speech about

07:52.800 --> 07:59.520
eating problems in young women. The newspapers were still very interested in Diana.

08:00.240 --> 08:04.000
She had very little private life and this was very hard for her.

08:05.520 --> 08:12.400
At a dinner on the 3rd of December 1993 at the Dorchester Hotel in London she made a speech.

08:13.680 --> 08:19.920
She said the newspaper and television reporters made her life very difficult. She had no private

08:19.920 --> 08:26.000
life and needed more time alone. She did not want to do so many things in public.

08:26.960 --> 08:33.120
She did not want to do so much charity work. Oliver Hall left his wife.

08:34.480 --> 08:41.920
But in January 1994 he went back to her. He did not want to leave his family for Diana.

08:43.760 --> 08:48.720
Then in March James Hewitt gave an interview to a reporter from the Daily Express.

08:50.160 --> 08:54.080
The newspaper printed the story of Hewitt's relationship with Diana.

08:55.520 --> 08:59.120
Now the British people knew about Diana's relationship with Hewitt.

09:00.640 --> 09:08.640
Later that year Hewitt published a book about his time with Diana. The book was called Princess in Love.

09:10.480 --> 09:16.720
People already knew about Diana's story from Andrew Morton's book. They felt very sorry for her.

09:17.680 --> 09:24.240
This made Charles very angry. So he decided to tell the British people about his life too.

09:25.760 --> 09:32.400
He asked a journalist, Jonathan Dimbleby, to write a biography, a book about Charles's life.

09:33.600 --> 09:40.160
He also did an interview with Jonathan Dimbleby on television. Many of Charles's friends did not

09:40.160 --> 09:46.880
want him to do the interview. It is not a good idea for the prince to talk about his personal life

09:46.880 --> 09:51.680
on television, they said. But Charles did not listen to his friends.

09:53.840 --> 10:01.280
The interview was on television on the 29th of June 1994. Charles talked about the British

10:01.280 --> 10:08.400
countryside and about his work with young people. But he also talked about a relationship with

10:08.400 --> 10:15.440
another woman. People thought this woman was Camilla Parker Bowles. Millions of people watched

10:15.440 --> 10:23.600
the interview. They were very shocked. While Charles was married to Diana, he had a girlfriend.

10:24.560 --> 10:29.760
Seven months later, Andrew and Camilla Parker Bowles divorced.

10:42.480 --> 10:45.600
Chapter 9 The Road to Divorce

10:46.400 --> 10:55.120
Diana went to the United States in October 1994. The American people liked her very much.

10:55.840 --> 11:03.760
Her visit was very successful. She met important people like Hillary Clinton and General Colin Powell.

11:05.280 --> 11:09.120
She talked to Hillary about her children and her plans for the future.

11:09.920 --> 11:15.440
Soon Diana returned to London. She started her charity work again.

11:16.800 --> 11:20.560
She visited two special hospitals for people with mental problems.

11:22.000 --> 11:26.640
Later in 1994, she went to see people in the poor parts of Paris.

11:27.920 --> 11:33.520
At the end of her visit, the French president, President Mitterrand, gave a dinner for her at

11:33.600 --> 11:41.120
the Palace of Versailles. He invited 900 people. Diana was not with her husband now,

11:41.920 --> 11:46.240
but she had some very good friends. These friends helped her a lot.

11:47.600 --> 11:54.320
One very close friend was Lucia Fletcher de Lima. Lucia lived in Washington with her husband,

11:55.200 --> 12:00.880
but she spoke to Diana a lot on the telephone. She gave Diana advice and helped her.

12:01.680 --> 12:09.520
Other good friends were Lady Annabelle Goldsmith, Rosa Monkton, and Carolyn Bartholomew, her old flatmate.

12:11.280 --> 12:18.960
In 1995, Diana visited 10 countries around the world. All of her visits were very successful.

12:20.000 --> 12:24.960
One was to Japan. Diana made a speech to the people in Japanese.

12:25.360 --> 12:34.800
Later, Diana went to Hong Kong. She raised a quarter of a million pounds for charities for young people and for medical work.

12:36.320 --> 12:42.240
Diana also went to Italy, France, New York, Russia, and Argentina.

12:43.920 --> 12:53.600
In 1994, Diana made only 10 public visits, but in 1995, she made 127.

12:55.920 --> 12:58.880
Diana's relationship with Oliver Hall was over.

13:00.000 --> 13:03.920
The newspapers started to write stories about a new male friend.

13:05.120 --> 13:10.960
This was Will Carling, an English rugby player, and captain of the England rugby team.

13:12.000 --> 13:16.000
People were shocked. Diana liked another married man.

13:16.640 --> 13:23.120
In 1995, Diana met Martin Beshear, a well-known journalist.

13:24.320 --> 13:28.560
Beshear worked for the BBC's television programme, Panorama.

13:29.520 --> 13:32.400
He wanted Diana to do an interview on television.

13:33.920 --> 13:38.960
The BBC showed the interview on the 20th of November 1995.

13:40.240 --> 13:42.720
Diana looked beautiful but sad.

13:43.680 --> 13:47.360
She wore black clothes and black makeup around her eyes.

13:48.880 --> 13:52.720
Diana talked about her relationship with Charles and the royal family.

13:53.440 --> 13:55.680
She talked about Camilla Parker Bowles.

13:57.040 --> 13:59.840
There were three of us in this marriage, she said.

14:01.200 --> 14:07.280
She talked about Andrew Morton's book, Her Bellemia, and her relationship with James Hewitt.

14:08.240 --> 14:11.680
I want to help people with problems, she said.

14:13.280 --> 14:16.160
15 million people in Britain watched the interview.

14:17.520 --> 14:20.480
Millions of other people around the world watched it too.

14:21.600 --> 14:27.040
They were shocked. Diana's friends thought the interview was a terrible mistake.

14:28.160 --> 14:30.480
The royal family were also very upset.

14:31.680 --> 14:36.320
After the interview, Princess Margaret did not want to be friends with Diana anymore.

14:38.240 --> 14:42.640
In December 1995, Diana had a letter from the Queen.

14:43.920 --> 14:46.640
The Queen wanted Charles and Diana to divorce.

14:47.600 --> 14:50.720
She was worried about her country and the royal family.

14:52.560 --> 14:58.640
Later, on the 15th of February 1996, Diana met the Queen at Buckingham Palace.

14:58.640 --> 15:04.720
I do not want to divorce, said Diana. I still love Charles.

15:06.320 --> 15:11.280
Diana and the Queen talked about William and Harry and about Diana's future.

15:12.880 --> 15:17.520
Later in February 1996, Diana met with Prince Charles.

15:18.480 --> 15:20.480
They talked about the end of their marriage.

15:21.840 --> 15:25.920
On the 28th of August 1996, they were divorced.

15:26.880 --> 15:34.160
After the divorce, Diana lost her title, her royal highness, and her special place in the royal family.

15:35.440 --> 15:38.960
She was now just Diana, Princess of Wales.

15:40.720 --> 15:43.840
I never wanted a divorce, Diana wrote.

15:45.040 --> 15:51.280
I always dreamed of a happy marriage, but the fairy tale marriage was over.

15:56.480 --> 16:02.800
In the last few years, Diana was married to the Queen, and she was married to the Queen.

16:03.920 --> 16:07.440
Chapter 10. Starting a new life

16:09.120 --> 16:13.120
Diana was alone, and she had to make a new life for herself.

16:14.560 --> 16:19.920
She knew many rich and famous people, but she did not only want to spend time with them,

16:20.880 --> 16:25.440
she wanted a normal life, and she wanted to help the poor and the sick.

16:27.120 --> 16:33.680
Diana had many beautiful dresses and other clothes, but she did not need these clothes now.

16:34.720 --> 16:39.760
They were from her old life with Prince Charles. She did not want to wear them again,

16:40.960 --> 16:46.240
but she did not know what to do with them. Then Prince William had a good idea.

16:46.240 --> 16:50.880
Sell the clothes and make money for charity, he said.

16:52.720 --> 17:00.560
Christie's a famous auction house helped Diana. At an auction, a lot of people come to see things

17:00.560 --> 17:06.160
that are for sale. The person who offers the most money for an object can buy it.

17:08.400 --> 17:14.640
In September 1996, a person from Christie's went to see Diana at Kensington Palace.

17:16.240 --> 17:22.480
They talked about the sale of Diana's clothes at an auction. Diana wanted the sale to be in New

17:22.480 --> 17:30.560
York. She wanted the money to help people with AIDS. Diana also wanted to help people in other

17:30.560 --> 17:38.720
countries. She was very worried about landmines. A landmine is a bomb which is put under the ground.

17:39.520 --> 17:42.640
It explodes when a person or car moves over it.

17:43.440 --> 17:49.200
Many countries use landmines in wars. Landmines are very dangerous.

17:50.240 --> 17:56.240
People, often women and children, die or lose arms or legs because of landmines.

17:57.600 --> 18:02.880
Many people did not know about landmines, and Diana wanted to tell the world about them.

18:04.000 --> 18:07.360
She wanted to stop countries from using landmines in war.

18:08.320 --> 18:16.240
She talked to the British Red Cross, and in January 1997, she went to Angola for the Red Cross.

18:17.440 --> 18:22.480
There was terrible war in Angola, and there were many landmines in that country.

18:24.320 --> 18:29.760
People who worked for the television company the BBC went with Diana and filmed her.

18:30.720 --> 18:37.520
She met people with terrible landmine injuries. She worked hard and visited dangerous places.

18:38.480 --> 18:44.000
She walked in parts of the countryside where there were landmines. But she was not afraid.

18:45.200 --> 18:49.520
She went to hospitals and talked to children with injuries from landmines.

18:50.400 --> 18:52.640
She sat with them and held their hands.

18:54.640 --> 18:57.680
Diana also wanted to help people with eating problems.

18:58.480 --> 19:02.720
In the UK, in May 1997, she made a speech.

19:03.920 --> 19:06.800
I don't have problems with bulimia anymore, she said.

19:07.760 --> 19:10.160
Diana looked beautiful and healthy.

19:11.680 --> 19:13.360
Diana was very busy.

19:14.640 --> 19:22.400
In May, she and Prince William went to lunch with the new British Prime Minister, Tony Blair and his family.

19:23.680 --> 19:25.600
They talked about Diana's future.

19:25.680 --> 19:30.960
In June, Diana flew to Washington to meet Hillary Clinton.

19:32.080 --> 19:38.320
Then she went to New York to meet Mother Teresa. She liked Mother Teresa's work very much.

19:40.240 --> 19:46.000
Later that year, in June, she flew back to New York for a party at Christie's auction house.

19:47.120 --> 19:53.440
The party was before the sale of Diana's clothes. The sale was a great success.

19:54.080 --> 20:02.960
All Diana's dresses sold for a total of $3,258,750.

20:03.840 --> 20:11.440
The top price was $222,500 for a dress.

20:12.480 --> 20:15.920
Diana wore this dress when she danced with John Travolta.

20:24.320 --> 20:29.680
Chapter 11

20:31.440 --> 20:32.080
New Love

20:33.920 --> 20:36.160
There was a new man in Diana's life.

20:37.840 --> 20:40.800
Diana knew a woman called Una Shanley Tofolo.

20:41.840 --> 20:45.440
Una's husband, Joseph, had a problem with his heart.

20:46.720 --> 20:53.120
In August 1995, he was very ill. He went to the Royal Brompton Hospital in London.

20:54.000 --> 20:55.440
He had a heart operation.

20:57.360 --> 21:03.680
On August the 31st, Una telephone Diana. Diana went quickly to the hospital.

21:04.720 --> 21:09.840
She met Joseph's doctors. One of them was Hasnut Khan.

21:10.880 --> 21:17.520
Hasnut Khan was from Pakistan. He was 36 years old and very good looking.

21:17.520 --> 21:24.080
Diana often went to the hospital. She met Hasnut Khan many times.

21:25.280 --> 21:31.040
She was very interested in his work. Sometimes she watched him doing operations.

21:32.560 --> 21:38.880
Diana and Hasnut Khan were good friends. Soon, they became more than friends.

21:40.880 --> 21:46.320
Diana often called Hasnut Khan at the hospital. But when she called him,

21:46.320 --> 21:52.560
she did not use her real name. Sometimes she called herself Dr. Armani.

21:54.240 --> 21:59.200
Sometimes Diana and Hasnut Khan had dinner in small restaurants in London.

22:00.560 --> 22:05.840
But Khan usually came to Kensington Palace. Diana was very happy.

22:07.920 --> 22:15.040
Diana was very much in love with Hasnut Khan. Khan cared about people and he saved lives.

22:16.000 --> 22:22.160
Diana liked this. She began reading medical books so she could talk to him about his work.

22:23.680 --> 22:31.040
Khan was also very kind to her. And he liked Diana the person, not because she was a princess.

22:32.800 --> 22:39.600
Hasnut Khan's religion was Islam. So Diana also began reading books about Islam.

22:40.480 --> 22:46.560
And she became very interested in Pakistan. She bought Pakistani women's clothes.

22:47.920 --> 22:53.840
Diana's good friend, Lady Annabelle Goldsmith, had a young and beautiful daughter,

22:53.840 --> 23:00.240
Jemima. Jemima was married to the famous Pakistani cricket player, Imran Khan.

23:01.360 --> 23:08.800
Imran Khan was interested in Pakistani politics. He also had a hospital in Pakistan for people

23:08.800 --> 23:15.840
with cancer, a serious illness. Diana became very friendly with Jemima Khan.

23:17.120 --> 23:20.240
She talked to her about marriage to a Pakistani man.

23:22.160 --> 23:27.440
Diana went to Lahore, Pakistan, in February and May of 1996.

23:28.880 --> 23:36.240
She visited Jemima and Imran Khan and Imran Khan's hospital. She talked to many children with

23:36.320 --> 23:43.600
cancer and helped them a lot. Many photographs appeared in the newspapers of Diana with sick

23:43.600 --> 23:52.960
children. At first, Diana and Hasnut's relationship was secret. But later the newspapers found out

23:52.960 --> 24:00.800
about it. Hasnut Khan was very unhappy. He did not want the newspapers to write stories about him

24:00.800 --> 24:08.240
and Diana. He did not want his photograph in all the newspapers. He did not want to be famous

24:08.240 --> 24:16.160
because he was Diana's lover. Diana wanted to marry Khan. But the most important thing in

24:16.160 --> 24:24.320
Hasnut Khan's life was his work. He wanted to be a good doctor and to work in Pakistan, his home

24:24.320 --> 24:33.680
country. He did not want to be Diana's husband. Diana and Khan's relationship finished. Diana

24:33.680 --> 24:42.480
still wanted to marry him. But she knew that they had no future. That same summer, Diana met another

24:42.880 --> 24:45.360
man, Dodi Al-Fayed.

24:57.760 --> 25:00.960
Chapter 12 The Last Summer

25:02.560 --> 25:06.160
Dodi Al-Fayed's father was Mohammed Al-Fayed.

25:07.120 --> 25:15.760
Mohammed Al-Fayed was Egyptian and he was very rich. He had nine houses, a private plane,

25:15.760 --> 25:26.160
a helicopter, many expensive cars and a film company. In 1979, he bought the Ritz Hotel in Paris.

25:27.120 --> 25:33.120
And in 1984, he bought the most famous shop in London. Harrods.

25:34.880 --> 25:40.480
Mohammed Al-Fayed liked British people. He wanted to be part of British society.

25:41.520 --> 25:48.800
He wanted famous people like Diana to be his friends. So in the summer of 1997,

25:49.520 --> 25:55.840
he invited Diana and her sons to stay with him and his family. They could stay at his home

25:55.840 --> 26:03.200
near Santa Fe in the south of France. Diana had no summer plans for herself and her sons.

26:04.160 --> 26:14.240
So she said yes to Mohammed. Mohammed bought a beautiful yacht, the Johnacal. It cost £15 million.

26:15.520 --> 26:23.680
16 sailors worked on the boat. Mohammed telephoned his son, Dodi. At that time,

26:23.760 --> 26:28.320
Dodi was in Paris with his fiancé, the woman he planned to marry.

26:29.440 --> 26:32.640
She was an American model called Kelly Fisher.

26:34.320 --> 26:38.400
Mohammed told his son to leave Kelly and come and meet Diana.

26:40.000 --> 26:47.360
On the 14th of July, he sent his private plane to Paris. The plane took Dodi to the family villa.

26:47.600 --> 26:56.240
Dodi fired was 42 years old. He had the life of a playboy. His father gave him lots of money

26:56.240 --> 27:04.080
and he spent it on having fun and driving fast cars. He was also successful with women

27:04.080 --> 27:11.600
because he was good looking and kind. On the 16th of July, Diana and the boys flew in

27:12.240 --> 27:20.640
Mohammed's private plane to France. They stayed in his villa, the Castel Santalene,

27:21.440 --> 27:28.000
and spent time on his yacht. The photographers followed Diana to the south of France.

27:29.360 --> 27:35.360
They waited in boats near Mohammed's villa. They took pictures of Diana by the swimming pool

27:36.000 --> 27:42.160
and having fun in the sea. The photographers saw Dodi with Diana,

27:42.800 --> 27:47.920
but they did not know who he was. They thought he was a sailor from the John Echal.

27:49.440 --> 27:55.520
They did not know he was Mohammed Al Fayed's son, but they saw that Diana looked very happy.

27:57.280 --> 28:02.800
Kelly Fisher, Dodi's fiancé, saw photos of Diana and Dodi in the newspapers.

28:03.680 --> 28:10.960
She was very angry. She called Dodi but he did not answer. So she telephoned Dodi's father,

28:10.960 --> 28:15.840
Mohammed. But Diana was more important for Mohammed than Kelly.

28:17.200 --> 28:22.240
Forget about Dodi, Mohammed told her, you and Dodi are finished.

28:24.480 --> 28:29.360
Diana wrote a letter to Dodi. She thanked him for a wonderful holiday together.

28:30.000 --> 28:37.040
Darling Dodi, she wrote, thank you for the most magical six days on the ocean waves.

28:39.440 --> 28:46.000
On the 20th of July, Diana flew back to London. There she met Hasnut Khan,

28:47.040 --> 28:53.600
but their relationship was finished. In late July, Diana flew back to Paris.

28:54.560 --> 29:01.280
She met Dodi for a day. On the 31st of July, she flew back to the John Echal.

29:02.720 --> 29:08.560
William and Harry were not with her this time. They were on holiday with Prince Charles in Scotland.

29:10.320 --> 29:18.320
Diana and Dodi went to Corsica and Sardinia on the John Echal. Diana was very happy and relaxed.

29:19.200 --> 29:25.840
But the photographers followed them and took photos. The newspapers in London paid a lot

29:25.840 --> 29:34.320
of money for these photos. On the 8th of August, Diana went to Bosnia to talk about landmines.

29:35.600 --> 29:40.000
She visited Sarajevo and met people with injuries from landmines.

29:41.440 --> 29:45.360
Then she went on holiday to Greece with her friend, Rosa Monkton.

29:46.160 --> 29:54.000
But Diana and Dodi spent time together too in August. They stayed together in London and on the John Echal.

29:54.960 --> 30:01.280
The photographers were there all the time. They came when Diana and Dodi had a romantic

30:01.280 --> 30:05.600
walk on a beach. They flew in helicopters over the John Echal.

30:07.440 --> 30:14.720
On the 30th of August, Diana and Dodi went to Paris. But the photographers found out their plans.

30:15.680 --> 30:21.520
The photographers waited for them at the airport. They followed their car on motorbikes,

30:21.520 --> 30:28.240
trying to take photographs. Diana and Dodi went to Dodi's apartment to dress for dinner.

30:29.120 --> 30:35.520
The photographers waited outside the apartment, shouting and pushing. Dodi was angry.

30:36.880 --> 30:41.600
When Diana and Dodi came out of the apartment, the photographers were still there.

30:42.240 --> 30:48.080
They got on their bikes and drove very near the car. It was very dangerous.

30:50.320 --> 30:54.800
A table was reserved for dinner at a restaurant called Che Benoit.

30:56.160 --> 31:01.440
But Dodi did not want the photographers to follow them there. So he changed their plans

31:02.240 --> 31:09.280
and decided to have dinner at the Ritz Hotel. They drove to the Ritz. But the photographers were

31:09.360 --> 31:18.160
there too. Diana got out of the car and ran inside. Dodi and Diana had dinner upstairs in the Ritz.

31:19.520 --> 31:27.120
At dinner, Dodi made a plan to lose the photographers. Dodi's car was at the front door of the hotel.

31:27.920 --> 31:34.880
But Dodi decided to use another car at the back door. The photographers did not know about this car.

31:35.120 --> 31:40.720
The assistant head of security at the Ritz was called Henri Paul.

31:42.160 --> 31:48.320
Dodi told Henri Paul about his plan. He wanted him to drive the secret car.

31:50.000 --> 31:56.640
Diana and Dodi left by the back door. Trevor Reese Jones, a man who worked for the

31:56.640 --> 32:04.960
fires and protected Diana, went too. Dodi sat in the back behind Henri Paul. Diana was on

32:04.960 --> 32:13.440
Dodi's right side. Nobody in the car wore a seat belt. At about midnight, Paul drove quickly away

32:13.440 --> 32:21.280
from the hotel. But the photographers soon saw the car. Quickly they got onto their motorbikes

32:21.280 --> 32:29.600
and followed it. Henri Paul tried to lose the photographers. He did not take the direct road,

32:29.600 --> 32:35.920
the Champs-Elysé, back to Dodi's apartment. He decided to drive down the tunnel under the

32:35.920 --> 32:46.240
plastama. Henri Paul was driving too fast and he had alcohol in his body. Only three minutes

32:46.240 --> 32:54.720
after leaving the Ritz hotel, the car crashed into part of the tunnel. Dodi and Paul were killed.

32:55.760 --> 32:59.440
But Trevor Reese Jones and Diana were still alive.

33:01.760 --> 33:07.920
About 10 to 15 photographers arrived in seconds and started taking photographs of Diana.

33:09.200 --> 33:15.280
Only two of them called for help on their mobile phones. People were very shocked

33:15.360 --> 33:21.120
because the photographers did not help the people in the car. When the police arrived,

33:21.120 --> 33:28.800
they arrested seven of the photographers. A doctor, Frederick Mallet, was in the tunnel.

33:30.320 --> 33:38.880
He tried to help Diana. Diana did not look badly hurt, but the injuries inside her body were terrible.

33:39.280 --> 33:46.320
The ambulances arrived. They took Diana to La Pitea's São Petrière hospital.

33:47.440 --> 33:54.160
But the doctors there could not save her. At 4 a.m. Paris time, on the morning of the 31st

33:54.160 --> 34:04.160
of August 1997, Diana died. The British ambassador in Paris, Sir Michael J, came to the hospital.

34:05.120 --> 34:10.640
He telephoned the Queen's assistant private secretary, Sir Robin Janverin, in London.

34:12.160 --> 34:20.080
Diana is dead, he said. Janverin told the Queen and Prince Philip.

34:20.080 --> 34:34.320
Chapter 13 The People's Princess

34:36.000 --> 34:41.920
People all over the world heard the sad and terrible news, but nobody could believe it.

34:43.120 --> 34:46.720
How could Diana be dead? It could not be true.

34:47.120 --> 34:52.880
Princess William and Harry were at Balmoral in Scotland, with Prince Charles and the Queen and

34:52.880 --> 35:00.080
Prince Philip. Prince Charles told them about their mother's death. Tony Blair was the new British

35:00.080 --> 35:07.520
Prime Minister. The morning after Diana's death, he spoke about Diana and the British people.

35:08.480 --> 35:14.800
They liked her. They loved her as one of the people, he said.

35:14.800 --> 35:23.600
She was the people's princess, and that's how she will stay, in all our hearts and memories forever.

35:26.320 --> 35:30.800
Prince Charles and Diana's two sisters, Sarah and Jane, flew to Paris.

35:31.600 --> 35:38.880
They brought Diana's body back to London. Sarah wanted a quiet funeral for Diana at the

35:38.880 --> 35:45.040
Spencer family home in all Thorpe, but thousands of people waited by the road from the airport.

35:46.160 --> 35:54.640
There was not going to be a quiet funeral. Diana's body was taken to the Chapel Royal at St. James's

35:54.720 --> 35:58.560
Palace. Then it was taken to Kensington Palace.

36:00.480 --> 36:07.120
Charles Spencer, Diana's brother, lived in South Africa. He flew to London immediately.

36:08.640 --> 36:15.840
Diana's mother, Frances, was at her home in Scotland on the Isle of Sile. She too came to London.

36:17.440 --> 36:24.080
But the royal family was still at Balmoral on holiday. The British people began to ask questions,

36:25.200 --> 36:29.840
why aren't the royal family here in London? They said, do they care?

36:30.720 --> 36:36.960
Said one popular British newspaper, The Sun. Where is the queen when the country needs her?

36:38.160 --> 36:43.200
Why doesn't the queen talk to the British people about Diana? Ask the people.

36:44.880 --> 36:52.560
People began to dislike the royal family. The royal family was cold and did not care about Diana,

36:52.640 --> 37:00.000
they said. People said these things, but still the queen and the royal family stayed in Scotland.

37:01.440 --> 37:08.640
People put flowers outside the gates of Kensington Palace. The number of flowers grew and grew.

37:09.920 --> 37:16.960
People wrote cards and left messages for Diana. They waited for hours to sign a special book

37:16.960 --> 37:26.320
to remember Diana. Then at last, on Friday the 5th of September, the royal family returned to London.

37:27.600 --> 37:31.920
The queen made a speech and the family walked in the streets with the people.

37:33.200 --> 37:36.640
Finally, they began to understand the feelings of the people.

37:39.200 --> 37:43.360
Diana's funeral was on the 6th of September 1997.

37:44.240 --> 37:50.640
More than 1 million people came to London and many more watched the funeral on television.

37:52.160 --> 37:57.920
Prince William and Prince Harry walked behind Diana's coffin, the box where her body was.

37:59.680 --> 38:02.800
Diana's favourite white flowers were on top of the coffin.

38:04.320 --> 38:11.840
Prince Harry, who was only 12 years old, wrote one word on a card. The word was mummy.

38:12.480 --> 38:19.440
This card was on the coffin too. When people saw the card, they felt very sad.

38:21.440 --> 38:25.840
The coffin went from Kensington Palace to Westminster Abbey for the funeral.

38:27.040 --> 38:32.240
Thousands of people stood quietly by the road. Many people cried.

38:33.920 --> 38:37.600
Famous people from all over the world came to the funeral service.

38:37.600 --> 38:46.320
Bill and Hillary Clinton came. There were actors like Tom Cruise, Tom Hanks and Nicole Kidman.

38:46.960 --> 38:51.200
There were singers like Sting, Elton John and George Michael.

38:52.320 --> 38:59.120
There were Diana's old school friends like Carolyn Bartholomew and her old headmistress from West

38:59.120 --> 39:07.360
Heath School. There were Diana's new friends like Lucia Fletcher de Lima. Hasnad Khan was

39:07.440 --> 39:13.680
there and Imran Khan and Jemima. And there were many people from Diana's charities.

39:15.280 --> 39:22.720
Elton John sang a beautiful song, Candle in the Wind. He first wrote it for Marilyn Monroe

39:23.280 --> 39:32.720
but wrote new words for Diana. Diana and Marilyn Monroe died at exactly the same age, 36.

39:33.600 --> 39:38.240
Diana's brother Charles made a speech at the funeral.

39:39.760 --> 39:47.600
Diana's name means Huntress, he said. But Diana became the most hunted woman in the world.

39:48.720 --> 39:56.080
Outside, thousands of people listened. When Charles finished, they began to clap their hands.

39:56.400 --> 40:03.200
After the funeral, the coffin went very slowly to Althorp, the Spencer family home.

40:04.560 --> 40:06.960
People in the streets of London threw flowers.

40:08.320 --> 40:12.400
At Althorp, Charles Spencer said, Diana is home.

40:15.040 --> 40:23.200
Diana is now buried in the ground on a small island. The island is in a lake in the garden at Althorp.

40:24.000 --> 40:31.680
There are trees all round the lake. It is the perfect place for a princess at peace.

40:44.240 --> 40:47.840
Chapter 14 After Diana's death

40:48.000 --> 40:52.480
The Diana Princess of Wales Memorial Fund

40:54.560 --> 41:01.840
The Diana Princess of Wales Memorial Fund was started on the 14th of September, 1997.

41:03.280 --> 41:11.120
When it began, there was 19 million pounds in the fund. Money that Diana left and money from

41:11.120 --> 41:17.440
Prince Charles was put into the fund. Money from the people of Britain and money from the

41:17.440 --> 41:25.520
sales of Sir Elton John's song, Candle in the Wind, was also put in. The fund gives money to

41:25.520 --> 41:33.920
people for three reasons. The first reason is to stop the use of landmines and to help people

41:34.000 --> 41:41.520
hurt by landmines. The second is to help people in Africa who are dying from an illness,

41:42.320 --> 41:51.440
for example, AIDS. The third is to give money to help young people in the UK with special difficulties.

41:53.360 --> 41:59.200
The president of the fund is Lady Sarah McCorkidale, Diana's oldest sister.

41:59.840 --> 42:03.040
Charles and Camilla

42:05.040 --> 42:10.560
Prince Charles married Camilla Parker Bowles on the 9th of April 2005.

42:11.920 --> 42:17.040
After the wedding, the Queen gave a party for Charles and Camilla at Windsor Castle.

42:18.080 --> 42:24.800
Later Charles and Camilla went to Scotland. Camilla's title is now Her Royal Highness,

42:24.800 --> 42:31.200
the Duchess of Cornwall. Sometimes Charles and Camilla carry out royal duties together.

42:33.760 --> 42:35.040
Concert for Diana

42:37.200 --> 42:46.000
On the 1st of July 2007, about 10 years after Princess Diana died, there was a concert for her in London.

42:46.960 --> 42:54.000
The 1st of July was Diana's birthday. Prince William and Prince Harry planned the concert.

42:55.040 --> 42:59.680
They invited many of the world's most famous singers and entertainers to come there.

43:00.720 --> 43:07.920
They invited Sir Elton John, the English National Ballet, Brian Ferry, Andrea Bocelli,

43:08.480 --> 43:16.240
Rod Stewart and take that. The concert was eight hours long and was very successful.

43:17.360 --> 43:23.600
People in 140 countries watched the concert on television or heard it on the radio.

43:24.960 --> 43:29.360
63,000 people came to Wembley Stadium to see the concert.

43:30.720 --> 43:34.320
At the end, a video of Diana as a child was shown.

43:35.840 --> 43:42.560
The music for the video was the song by the pop group Queen. These are the days of our lives.

43:43.840 --> 43:46.160
There is now a DVD of the concert.

43:48.160 --> 43:53.600
The money from the concert went to charities chosen by Prince William and Prince Harry.

43:54.800 --> 43:59.600
The charities were the Diana Princess of Wales Memorial Fund,

44:00.560 --> 44:08.320
Centipoint Charity for the Homeless and Centibale. A charity started in April 2006

44:08.320 --> 44:13.920
by Prince Harry and Prince Ciosio of Lesotho, a small country in South Africa.

44:15.440 --> 44:18.960
This charity helps children and young people in Lesotho.

44:20.000 --> 44:23.920
There are many children in Lesotho whose parents have died of AIDS.

44:25.600 --> 44:32.960
Diana is dead, but her memory lives on. People all around the world still want

44:32.960 --> 44:39.520
to see photographs and read books about her. They still want to know about the beautiful

44:39.520 --> 44:45.040
and caring princess who touched people's hearts all over the world.

44:54.800 --> 45:00.800
